						               													<description>This is a roll-and-move board game, which merges the gameplay of Monopoly with Casino &amp;quot;mini-games.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On a player's turn, they roll two dice and move clock-wise around a board, and take the action of the spot they land on.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a player lands on a property, and it is unowned, they may purchase it. If it is owned, then they must play the owner rent money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If they land on &amp;quot;Tough Luck&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Jackpot&amp;quot; card spots, the player takes a card from the corresponding card pile and follows the instructions on the chosen card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The unique aspect of the game is that if you land on a &amp;quot;Casino&amp;quot; spot, then the player plays a Casino &amp;quot;mini-game.&amp;quot; There are four mini-games: Roulette, Black Jack, Craps, and slots. (The game comes with a small roulette wheel, and dice to replicate slot machines.) Players can place bets on these games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to reach $35,000 (or the person with the most money after a set amount of time) is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
